= Installed Mediawiki Extensions =

Apart from our own original upgrades, we have hand-picked and installed numerous extensions to introduce more features to all users and to increase accessibility. The pre-installed extensions of the MediaWiki standard installation are omitted here for brevity.

# [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:CodeMirror '''CodeMirror'''] improves the editor experience with optional syntax highlighting
# [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:Comments '''Comments'''] allows user comments on pages where the special comments-tag is present
# [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:ContactPage '''ContactPage'''] offers a comprehensive and easy way for visitors to contact our team
# [https://github.com/Kicksecure/mediawiki-extensions-CookieToBodyClass '''CookieToBodyClass'''] is a MediaWiki extension '''created by our team'''. This allows developers to mirror cookies as a class for the body element, which is used to prevent "style jumps" when the page is loading. Here is the [[Dev/mediawiki#Extension_CookieToBodyClass|documentation for CookieToBodyClass]]
# [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:CookieWarning '''CookieWarning'''] implements the EU-mandatory warning for users that cookies are used
# [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:CSS '''CSS'''] allows custom CSS to be added to specific pages by developers to improve the user experience
# [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:DarkMode '''DarkMode'''] offers the option for users to view the page in dark mode / night mode
# [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:DisableAccount '''DisableAccount'''] gives admins the power to ban malicious accounts and thereby secure the integrity of the wiki
# [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:FlaggedRevs '''Flagged Revisions'''] offers visitors, even anonymous ones, the ability to edit our pages and contribute, and gives these contributions to editors and admins for a safe revision before publication
# [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:HeadScript '''HeadScript'''] allows us to implement custom CSS, JS, favicons, other libraries, fontAwesome, etc. for more functionality on the wiki
# [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:LinkSuggest '''LinkSuggest'''] suggests links to editors, making the editing process a little bit faster and more efficient
# [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:LinkToArchive '''LinkToArchive'''] adds to external links on the wiki an automatic link of the Web Archive version of this URL
# [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:Lockdown '''Lockdown'''] improves wiki security by offering a more finely grained restriction model
# [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:MsUpload '''MsUpload'''] introduces a handy drag-and-drop upload area for files to improve the editor experience
# [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:NewSignupPage '''New Signup Page'''] enhances MediaWiki's default signup page
# [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:Popups '''Previews'''] displays preview popups when the user hovers over a link
# [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:RevisionSlider '''Revision Slider'''] adds a more comfortable, more practical slider interface to the diff view for editors
# [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:RottenLinks '''Rotten Links'''] helps keep the wiki clean by preventing dead links on the wiki by showing the admin a table of all external links on the wiki with their status
# [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:UserMerge '''User Merge'''] allows the admin to merge different user accounts, for example, if a user created duplicate accounts by accident, account reconciliation, and other scenarios alike that might occur for contributors and other users
# [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:Widgets '''Widgets'''] offers developers the opportunity to add true HTML fragments to our pages. This is used to create well-designed special pages for our users that would not be achievable with the standard wiki syntax
# [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:WikiSEO '''WikiSEO'''] allows us to create and maintain high-level SEO optimizations for our wiki so they can be found more easily by new users

